title: Tassie MPs approve build of new stadium
description: MPs in the Tasmania's House of Assembly have voted in favour of a new $1.13 billion stadium at Macquarie Point. #tasmania #stadium #parliament #houseofassembly #macquariepoint

title: SA could follow Victoria in signing treaty with its Indigenous people
description: South Australia looks set to follow Victoria's lead in establishing a treaty with its Indigenous people after the state's Deputy Premier voicing his support for it. #treaty #Victoria #SouthAustralia #premier #news

title: Leonardo DiCaprio honours Jane Goodall at funeral service
description: Actor Leonardo DiCaprio has honoured the life and legacy of British primatologist and conservationist Jane Goodall. Mourners gathered at Washington National Cathedral, Washington DC to farewell Goodall who died last month at the age of 91.   Family, friends and movie stars attended to pay their respects to the conservationist, famous for her study of chimpanzees. #JaneGoodall #LeonardoDiCaprio #conservationist #WashingtonDC #service

title: Guilty plea in Molly Ticehurst murder case | 7NEWS
description: Daniel Billings pleaded guilty to murdering 28-year-old childcare worker Molly Ticehurst in her Forbes home 18 months ago while he was on bail and facing domestic violence charges. The guilty plea at Goulburn court brought emotional relief to Ticehurst's family and the Forbes community, who had been waiting through multiple adjournments for this outcome. Molly's death triggered new domestic violence laws across New South Wales. title: Daniel Billings pleads guilty to murdering ex-partner Molly Ticehurst in Forbes, NSW
description: Daniel Billings has pleaded guilty to murdering his ex-partner, young mum Molly Ticehurst, in her Forbes home in the Central West of NSW. Billings was on bail at the time of the killing and was facing charges relating to his horrific treatment of Molly.  If you or someone you know is impacted by sexual assault, domestic or family violence, call 1800RESPECT on 1800 737 732 or visit 1800RESPECT.org.au  #mollyticehurst #hernameismolly #crime #forbes #nsw

title: National child safety checks get $37m boost | 7NEWS
description: The federal government is investing $37 million to create a near real-time national Working with Children Check system that will notify all states and territories when someone's criminal history changes. The enhanced system will enable national bans on workers from childcare centres, schools, sports clubs and churches when their approval status is revoked in any jurisdiction. Attorney General Michelle Rowland announced the plan at a meeting with state and territory attorneys-general in Brisbane, with the expanded system expected to be operational by the end of the year. title: Victoria introduces tough new retail crime laws | 7NEWS
description: New laws in Victoria will introduce jail terms of up to five years for assaulting or threatening retail, hospitality and transport workers, with the legislation set to take effect by Christmas. The measures also include up to 25 years jail for ram raiding shopfronts and workplace protection orders to ban repeat offenders from specific businesses. Victoria recorded 82,000 retail crime incidents last year, representing a 30% increase. title: Wedding bus driver loses appeal against sentence | 7NEWS
description: Brett Button lost his Supreme Court appeal against his 32-year prison sentence for driving a wedding bus under the influence of opiates that crashed in the NSW Hunter Valley in June 2023. The crash killed 10 people and injured 25 others, making it one of Australia's deadliest road accidents. Button will be eligible for parole in 2048.
